Pimentel Sees Inflation as Brazil’s Top Priority, Estado Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-04-30T14:16:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/pimentel-sees-inflation-as-brazil-s-top-priority-estado-says.html
The Brazilian government biggest
priority is fighting inflation, even if this exacerbates the
real’s overvaluation in the short term, Development Minister
Fernando Pimentel said at the World Economic Forum yesterday in
Rio de Janeiro, Estado de Sao Paulo newspaper  reported .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
